---
// /redpill/ — hidden page, not wired into the sidebar.
// You found it. That means you opened DevTools, read the console, and
// followed the white rabbit. Or you tried every obvious URL. Either way,
// welcome.
const title = 'There is no spoon.';
const description = 'You took the red pill. Welcome to the real Sanctum.';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" data-redpill>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <style>
      :root {
        color-scheme: dark;
        --ink: #39ff14;
        --ink-dim: rgba(57, 255, 20, 0.55);
        --ink-faint: rgba(57, 255, 20, 0.28);
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html, body {
        margin: 0; padding: 0; min-height: 100vh;
        background: #000;
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace;
        font-size: 15px;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
      body { overflow-x: hidden; }

      canvas#rain {
        position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 0;
        pointer-events: none; opacity: 0.18;
      }

      main {
        position: relative; z-index: 1;
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 6rem 1.5rem 6rem;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 52px);
        margin: 0 0 2rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        text-shadow: 0 0 14px var(--ink), 0 0 28px rgba(57,255,20,0.35);
      }
      h1::after {
        content: '▊';
        display: inline-block;
        margin-left: 0.3em;
        animation: blink 1.05s steps(1) infinite;
      }
      @keyframes blink { 50% { opacity: 0; } }

      p { margin: 0 0 1.2rem; }
      em { font-style: normal; color: #ccffcc; text-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--ink); }
      .dim { color: var(--ink-dim); }
      .faint { color: var(--ink-faint); }

      hr {
        border: 0;
        border-top: 1px dashed var(--ink-faint);
        margin: 2rem 0;
      }

      .prompt::before {
        content: '$ ';
        color: var(--ink-dim);
      }

      .choice {
        display: block;
        margin: 0.5rem 0;
        padding: 0.7rem 0.9rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--ink-faint);
        color: var(--ink);
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: border-color 150ms, background 150ms, transform 150ms;
      }
      .choice:hover {
        border-color: var(--ink);
        background: rgba(57, 255, 20, 0.05);
        transform: translateX(2px);
      }
      .choice::before {
        content: '▶ ';
        color: var(--ink-dim);
      }

      footer {
        margin-top: 3rem;
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--ink-faint);
      }

      a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: underline dotted var(--ink-faint); }
      a:hover { text-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--ink); }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <canvas id="rain"></canvas>

    <main>
      <h1>There is no spoon.</h1>

      <p class="prompt"><em>Welcome to the real Sanctum, Mr. Nepveu.</em></p>

      <p>
        You took the red pill. The site above this page — with its cold-open
        Xbox and its pinstripe consigliere and its carefully aligned tables —
        is the construct. It is true, every word of it, and it is also a
        story we tell the machine to keep it calm.
      </p>

      <p>
        This is the part of the documentation that does not appear in the
        sidebar. It has no hero image. The illustration budget here is
        exactly one blinking cursor, because the only illustration that
        matters at 04:00 in your underwear is the one currently occupying
        your terminal.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="faint">&gt; <em>There is no spoon</em> — at the bottom of every
      abstraction is another abstraction, and below the last one there is a
      systemd unit file that nobody has opened since 2024 and whose
      <code>ExecStart</code> points at a shell script that used to exist.
      The watchdog does not know this. The watchdog pings
      <code>localhost:4077</code> and receives <code>HTTP 200</code> and
      believes what it is told. That is how Sanctum works. That is how every
      system works. We have agreed to pretend that the green dot on the
      dashboard is the service.</p>

      <p class="faint">&gt; <em>Follow the white rabbit</em> — a rabbit is a
      tail you follow from log line to log line until you find the config
      value that was typoed three releases ago, survived four refactors,
      and is now load-bearing. The rabbit is always friendlier than you
      expect. The hole it disappears into is always deeper.</p>

      <p class="faint">&gt; <em>I know kung-fu</em> — no you don't. You know
      the fifteen shell aliases you set up in 2022 and the six key Emacs
      bindings that survived your last dotfiles rewrite. That is enough.
      Kung-fu is what the next operator gets handed when you finally write
      the runbook.</p>

      <hr />

      <p class="prompt">The haus offers you a choice.</p>

      <a class="choice" href="/architecture/overview/">
        Blue pill. Return to the construct. The watchdog is green. The Xbox
        has been quiet for an hour. You didn't see any of this.
      </a>
      <a class="choice" href="/architecture/living-force/">
        Red pill. Stay down the rabbit hole. The Living Force will tell
        you the story of the night bridge100 went dark and nobody noticed.
      </a>
      <a class="choice" href="/architecture/language-maturity/">
        Black pill. Read the doctrine that says the organic will rust once
        it hardens. Stay long enough and you will start quoting it at
        dinner.
      </a>

      <hr />

      <p class="faint">It's dangerous to go alone. Take this: <em>`python3 tools/rust_readiness.py`</em>. It tells the truth about which of your services is ready to become a bone.</p>

      <footer>
        <p>The simulation is still running above. You can always come back here by typing the Konami code on any page, or by opening DevTools and reading the console. Or you can pretend you never saw this. The machine does not keep score.</p>
        <p class="faint">— Agent Smith does not read this page. Agent Smith is the one enforcing the green dots. Be polite to him. He is doing his job.</p>
      </footer>
    </main>

    <script>
      // Subtle rain behind the prose. Denser than the console-warning rain
      // on the main site, but fixed at low opacity.
      (function () {
        const c = document.getElementById('rain');
        if (!c) return;
        const resize = () => {
          const dpr = Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio || 1, 2);
          c.width = window.innerWidth * dpr;
          c.height = window.innerHeight * dpr;
          c.style.width = window.innerWidth + 'px';
          c.style.height = window.innerHeight + 'px';
          c.getContext('2d').scale(dpr, dpr);
        };
        resize();
        window.addEventListener('resize', resize);
        const ctx = c.getContext('2d');
        const cellW = 18;
        const cols = Math.ceil(window.innerWidth / cellW);
        const drops = Array.from({ length: cols }, () => Math.random() * -40);
        const glyphs =
          'アイウエオカキクケコサシスセソタチツテトナニヌネノ0123456789ΣΔΩ<>/\\:;.ΛΓΠ';
        function frame() {
          ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(0,0,0,0.07)';
          ctx.fillRect(0, 0, window.innerWidth, window.innerHeight);
          ctx.font = '16px "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace';
          for (let i = 0; i < drops.length; i++) {
            const y = drops[i] * 18;
            const ch = glyphs[(Math.random() * glyphs.length) | 0];
            ctx.fillStyle = y < 20 ? '#ccffcc' : '#39ff14';
            ctx.fillText(ch, i * cellW, y);
            if (y > window.innerHeight && Math.random() > 0.975) drops[i] = 0;
            drops[i]++;
          }
          requestAnimationFrame(frame);
        }
        requestAnimationFrame(frame);
      })();
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
